The paper deals with sponsored search relevance, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed approach involves using neural networks, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of tri-letter representation for queries is also a technique used in text classification and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of embeddings, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV).
